  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    BuilderStyle
    Annotated abstract class (let's suppose it's named AMyClass) will be used as template for generating a corresponding immutable class named MyClass, along with a builder to create instances of it.
    BuilderStylePublic
    Same as BuilderStyle but this one will force the generated immutable class to be public.
    SimpleStyle
    Annotated abstract class (let's suppose it's named AMyClass) will be used as template for generating a corresponding immutable class named MyClass.
